1
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:31,880
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,190 --> 00:01:34,880
[Episode 13]

3
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,060
Jiale!

4
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:50,640
What's wrong? Why are you pouting?

5
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,570
Are you unhappy?

6
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,880
I want to go back to my mom's place today.

7
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:56,150
Why?

8
00:01:58,940 --> 00:02:04,720
[The First Military Rule Came Into Being]

9
00:01:59,479 --> 00:02:01,000
Your mom's been busy recently,

10
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,930
so she asked you to stay in my place
for a few more days.

11
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:05,190
And you...

12
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:07,480
Didn't you say you wanted to play squash?

13
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:11,300
[The Story of Half a Blanket]

14
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:09,610
I've already booked the venue for you.

15
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:14,080
I saw that video.

16
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:17,420
How did you see it?

17
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,770
You're worried about her, right?

18
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:31,630
She's very brave.

19
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,000
She totally slayed this.

20
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,579
I mean, she's amazing.

21
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,230
You didn't know about this before?

22
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,200
Nope.

23
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:44,540
Well,

24
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:45,960
if I had known this back then,

25
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,490
I definitely would have...

26
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:56,800
That's just how your mom is.

27
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,030
Whatever she's going through,

28
00:02:58,030 --> 00:02:59,079
she will only keep it to herself

29
00:02:59,079 --> 00:03:00,480
and not tell anyone else.

30
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:02,760
She surely won't tell Grandma either.

31
00:03:05,530 --> 00:03:07,300
I want to call my mom.

32
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:10,010
Go ahead.

33
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,970
Hello, the subscriber you dialed is
powered off.

34
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,240
Her phone is powered off.

35
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,860
Maybe she wants some time alone.

36
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:33,579
Give her some space.

37
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:38,900
[The Red Army Boy Who Never Gave Up]

38
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,200
Say it.

39
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,360
Say that it's what you want me to do,

40
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:03,880
and it's what you wish for.

41
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:08,400
It's...

42
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,460
It's

43
00:04:10,490 --> 00:04:11,860
what I want you to do.

44
00:04:18,279 --> 00:04:19,690
It's what I wish for.

45
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:11,900
Who is it?

46
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,270
Ling...

47
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:31,690
I'm guilty. I'm so sorry.

48
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,230
I'm guilty.

49
00:05:34,659 --> 00:05:35,960
Ling.

50
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,740
Ling, I'm guilty.

51
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,720
I'm a sinner.

52
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,760
I'm guilty.

53
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,360
I owe you an apology.

54
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,950
I'm sorry.

55
00:05:49,970 --> 00:05:51,080
I'm so sorry.

56
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:52,590
Ling,

57
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,140
I'm guilty.

58
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:57,210
I'm guilty.

59
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:05,410
I'm so sorry.

60
00:06:06,270 --> 00:06:09,180
Why didn't you tell me before?

61
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,270
I'm sorry.

62
00:06:15,010 --> 00:06:17,050
I'm sorry.

63
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:23,460
Sorry, Ling.

64
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,920
I'm so sorry.

65
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,909
I don't even remember

66
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:47,330
when I bathed you like this last time.

67
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,740
When I was 12.

68
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,140
It's been ages.

69
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,280
It's all my fault.

70
00:07:06,980 --> 00:07:09,380
I was the one who pushed you
into the fire pit

71
00:07:10,890 --> 00:07:13,150
and even saw that beast as my benefactor,

72
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,850
letting him bully you over and over again.

73
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,750
It was the punishment for me.

74
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,360
It was all my fault.

75
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:35,730
I got Dad killed.

76
00:07:37,070 --> 00:07:38,850
I ruined this family.

77
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,480
It was karma catching up with me.

78
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:44,680
No.

79
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,960
It's not like that, Ling.

80
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:49,290
That's not the case.

81
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:52,460
It was me

82
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,480
who couldn't let go

83
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,810
and dragged you into it.

84
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,580
Actually, I know...

85
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,800
you were not the one to blame

86
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,200
for your dad's accident.

87
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,500
But at that time,

88
00:08:08,390 --> 00:08:09,980
I couldn't get over it.

89
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:11,680
I couldn't move on.

90
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:14,370
If I hadn't found someone
to take it out on,

91
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:16,870
I just couldn't have survived.

92
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,070
I don't deserve to be a mother.

93
00:08:21,070 --> 00:08:22,240
Ling, I don't deserve to be your mom.

94
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,000
Hit me.

95
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:23,750
Come on.

96
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:24,480
Hit me.

97
00:08:25,310 --> 00:08:26,430
Hate me.

98
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:28,600
Just hate me.

99
00:08:29,270 --> 00:08:31,000
I don't deserve to be your mom.

100
00:08:47,150 --> 00:08:48,480
Go home with me

101
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,170
during the Spring Festival.

102
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:54,530
Let's have your dad laid to rest in peace.

103
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,130
He'll be proud of you,

104
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,410
just like I am.

105
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,660
Why isn't Ding Zhibo in that ward anymore?

106
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:55,520
Where did he go?

107
00:09:55,670 --> 00:09:56,670
He got discharged long ago.

108
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:57,870
He left on the day of the accident.

109
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:58,730
Where did he go?

110
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:00,960
He went abroad, right?

111
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,750
People like him

112
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:03,150
would be better off dead.

113
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,120
Sorry,

114
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:13,720
the subscriber you dialed is

115
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,250
unavailable at the moment.

116
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,690
Please try again later.

117
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:22,360
Sorry,

118
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,000
the subscriber you dialed is

119
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,530
unavailable at the moment.

120
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,930
Please try again later.

121
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:47,750
Mom.

122
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,280
You're awake.

123
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:59,500
There's no food left in the fridge.

124
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:01,360
Go to the market with me, will you?

125
00:11:07,930 --> 00:11:09,060
It's not your fault.

126
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:13,550
We should live

127
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:15,870
without shame.

128
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:17,770
Let's go.

129
00:11:19,540 --> 00:11:26,230
[Fresh fruit & vegetable]

130
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,480
This shop sells fresh ingredients!

131
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,440
Take a look.

132
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:23,570
They're all fresh.

133
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:24,000
Yes.

134
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,720
Are you shopping with your daughter?

135
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,120
Yes.

136
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,630
You're so close.

137
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:28,560
So sweet.

138
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:29,440
Yes.

139
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,230
So happy.

140
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:32,460
Do you want these?

141
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:35,500
Let's buy one bunch.

142
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:45,230
[My Farm]

143
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:46,240
We've got some bamboo shoots.

144
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,040
I'll make the yanduxian for you.

145
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,280
Do you like it?

146
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,150
Anything is fine.

147
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:51,680
What else do you want to eat?

148
00:11:52,390 --> 00:11:53,570
Don't cook too much.

149
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,570
It's okay.

150
00:12:05,190 --> 00:12:06,180
[Hello, Ms. Yan Ling.
I'm a journalist from Lihai Weekly.

151
00:12:06,210 --> 00:12:08,080
[I'm really hoping
to have an interview with you.]

152
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,110
Just ignore all this crap.

153
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:23,740
[Luo Liang]

154
00:12:24,930 --> 00:12:26,650
[Luo Liang]

155
00:12:29,530 --> 00:12:33,900
[Springtime for the Wild Lily] [Courage]

156
00:12:40,390 --> 00:12:41,390
No matter what...

157
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,960
I want to say goodbye to you properly.

158
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:49,320
[Springtime for the Wild Lily]

159
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:52,550
Yan Ling.

160
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:55,550
From now on,

161
00:12:58,870 --> 00:13:00,130
I wish you all the best.

162
00:13:10,910 --> 00:13:13,640
When I held you in my arms
in the hospital that day,

163
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:16,630
I was sure about my feelings.

164
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,270
But later,

165
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:24,450
I could also feel

166
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:28,090
you're gradually
distancing yourself from me.

167
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:28,790
Love

168
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,020
or healing,

169
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,610
we made a different choice.

170
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:12,400
Thank you for your CDs.

171
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,570
I saw the news.

172
00:14:18,410 --> 00:14:19,230
You're brave.

173
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:21,880
and awesome.

174
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,760
The last time we met,

175
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:31,790
you said

176
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:34,270
we made a different choice.

177
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:39,150
If I say I made my choice

178
00:14:40,370 --> 00:14:41,900
because I don't deserve it,

179
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:43,750
can you get it?

180
00:14:45,410 --> 00:14:46,870
When I was still a minor,

181
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:49,870
I was with a man

182
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,240
old enough to be my dad.

183
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,740
I stuck with him

184
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:01,260
so as to vent my feelings
of missing and guilt

185
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,540
to my dad.

186
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,400
I feel ashamed

187
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:13,460
not only because I was
in a relationship with him,

188
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:17,750
but also because I thought

189
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,300
it was love during the whole process.

190
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,200
From high school,

191
00:15:26,390 --> 00:15:27,270
to university,

192
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,290
and to graduate school,

193
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,830
I had always regarded
this peculiar relationship

194
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:35,670
as love.

195
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,400
When I felt he was pulling away from me,

196
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:41,550
I even bought a new dress

197
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,520
and went to meet him in it.

198
00:15:44,670 --> 00:15:45,650
I saw him

199
00:15:47,270 --> 00:15:49,320
with a girl who was 15 or 16 years old,

200
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,640
just like how he was with me
in the beginning.

201
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,840
At that moment, it suddenly dawned on me

202
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:09,720
that what he felt

203
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:12,960
for me wasn't some unique love.

204
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,480
I was simply a prey

205
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,560
of his lust

206
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:21,840
for youth and his quirk.

207
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:27,920
That wasn't your fault.

208
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:30,630
No.

209
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:34,440
I'm terrible.

210
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,480
I got blotto.

211
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,670
Then Lu found me.

212
00:16:58,110 --> 00:16:59,800
He was my most trusted senior.

213
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:04,510
But I mistook him for...

214
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,300
I bought this dress because of you.

215
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,329
I got dressed up specifically for you!

216
00:17:13,510 --> 00:17:14,109
Yan Ling! Yan Ling!

217
00:17:14,109 --> 00:17:15,550
I'll tear it apart!

218
00:17:15,589 --> 00:17:16,000
Don't...

219
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:16,800
Don't do this.

220
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:17,800
Yan Ling!

221
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:19,300
Yan Ling.

222
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:20,480
Don't.

223
00:17:24,609 --> 00:17:25,920
I hurt myself.

224
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,350
And I hurt Lu.

225
00:17:38,550 --> 00:17:39,410
I can't believe

226
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:43,400
I even wore a new dress to meet that guy.

227
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:46,910
I was like a cheap prostitute,
begging for love.

228
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:52,430
Don't talk about yourself like that.

229
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:54,550
It was his fault.

230
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,640
He took advantage of you

231
00:18:07,310 --> 00:18:08,240
at your weakest.

232
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:14,080
He used your guilt over your dad's death

233
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,920
and your abnormal relationship
with your mother

234
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:20,120
to become the only pillar in your heart.

235
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,070
If you hadn't told yourself

236
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:23,000
that it was love,

237
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,200
you couldn't have made it through.

238
00:18:32,460 --> 00:18:34,920
After I got pregnant
with Lu's child, Jiale,

239
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:38,080
I thought

240
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,970
I had finally gotten rid of him.

241
00:18:42,310 --> 00:18:43,840
I took a year off from school

242
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:45,360
and gave birth to Jiale.

243
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,180
Then I went on to do a PhD

244
00:18:49,460 --> 00:18:51,060
and stayed to work at school.

245
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:54,020
I told myself

246
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,690
I wanted to start over.

247
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,100
I wanted to be a good mother

248
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:01,920
and a good teacher.

249
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:04,690
I wanted to be a good person.

250
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:14,510
In my eyes,

251
00:19:16,230 --> 00:19:17,830
you're always a good person.

252
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:34,750
In order to pass

253
00:19:34,750 --> 00:19:36,210
the core assessment of PUA

254
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,370
to get the evidence,

255
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:39,920
I filmed a video with Lu.

256
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,260
That kind of video?

257
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:49,670
Of course, it's not true.

258
00:19:53,790 --> 00:19:55,710
If it works

259
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,170
and can help avenge Leilei,

260
00:20:00,590 --> 00:20:01,720
I'm willing to do it.

261
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:18,490
Is this your whole story?

262
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:24,590
Why did you come to me today?

263
00:20:27,790 --> 00:20:29,320
Why did you tell me all this?

264
00:20:36,510 --> 00:20:37,770
I've never

265
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:40,650
ever been in a real relationship.

266
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:45,740
I can't even trust my own feelings

267
00:20:47,130 --> 00:20:48,520
or know what love is.

268
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,380
But after I met you,

269
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,580
I really wanted to tell you...

270
00:21:04,070 --> 00:21:05,400
Don't leave me.

271
00:21:07,550 --> 00:21:09,000
Don't leave me alone.

272
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,600
Don't go!

273
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,880
Don't leave me!

274
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:19,790
Don't leave me alone again!

275
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,520
You've suffered.

276
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:57,950
Poor thing.

277
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:22,220
I love you.

278
00:23:11,470 --> 00:23:12,700
I never knew

279
00:23:13,950 --> 00:23:15,700
I could be so happy.

280
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,020
Me, too.

281
00:23:44,850 --> 00:23:45,710
Hello, Ms. Yan.

282
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,110
Yan Ling!

283
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:00,440
Mrs. Feng.

284
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:06,000
Dear, you've suffered.

285
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:08,920
How have you been through all these years?

286
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:10,560
Luckily,

287
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:12,160
I'm still alive.

288
00:24:12,330 --> 00:24:13,960
I know there are bad guys

289
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,210
and jerks like this in the world.

290
00:24:15,210 --> 00:24:16,270
But I didn't expect

291
